body.p: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF } No. 6203 JOHN MATTHEWS } ORDER FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS

On motion of the United States Attorney IT IS HEREBY ORDERED, ADJUDGED and DECREED that the time in which the United States may prosecute an appeal is hereby extended ten days and the petition is will not be discharged but remanded to the from the Commissioner of Immigration custody is stated for ten days unless he is released on bond as heretofore provided.
Dones in open court this 13th day of October, 1921
IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON NORTHERN DIVISION
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF JOHN MATTHEWS FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS
FILED IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT Western District of Washington Northen Division
F.M. Harshberger, Clerk By S.E. Leitch Deputy
